env PAGER=cat man timing_report_analysis_summary_csv_extended_new_ format
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_report_...ded_new_format(25.10)  timing_report_...ded_new_format(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_analysis_summary_csv_extended_new_format

Syntax
       timing_report_analysis_summary_csv_extended_new_format

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Keeps the analysis summary CSV extended report in sync with the summary
       timing  report.  These  reports  are  available when the respective re-
       port_timing parameters are specified:

              * -analysis_summary_csv_extended_file

              * -analysis_summary_file

       When set to true (and when the report_timing  -analysis_summary_csv_ex-
       tended_file  parameter  is specified), the column name sequence will be
       from fromClk to toClk, that is, fromClk will be printed first, and then
       toClk. Also, the timing report will show "-", if toClk  or  fromClk  is
       not   present  (and  when  the  report_analysis_summary  -expanded_sum-
       mary_clocks parameter is set to false).

       When set to false, the missing toClk or fromClk column will  be  repre-
       sented as "*".

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

